<div id="review_31683952" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/31683952" />
    <a title="Lamski Kikita" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1439240-lamski-kikita"><img alt="Lamski Kikita" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1321835207p2/1439240.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/31683952?book_show_action=true">Aug 31, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lamski Kikita" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lamski Kikita" href="/user/show/1439240-lamski-kikita">Lamski Kikita</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer31683952" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4555924003313085161">Are humans naturally good or bad? We all struggle with the same question every single day in our daily dealings with people. Between angels and demons, people who help us and those who hurt us, we still cannot find the answer.<br/><br/>Chantal Prym is stuck in one man&apos;s struggle to justify his loss and his wager with the devil. It all falls on her shoulders to not only save her village, prevent her people from committing a crime they have deemed justifiable, but to bring back the light of angels and defea</span>
  <span id="freeText4555924003313085161" style="display:none">Are humans naturally good or bad? We all struggle with the same question every single day in our daily dealings with people. Between angels and demons, people who help us and those who hurt us, we still cannot find the answer.<br /><br />Chantal Prym is stuck in one man's struggle to justify his loss and his wager with the devil. It all falls on her shoulders to not only save her village, prevent her people from committing a crime they have deemed justifiable, but to bring back the light of angels and defeat all of the proud devils to win one more battle for good's sake.<br /><br />Another one of Coelho's masterpieces, but very different from the alchemist, on the river piedra, the Valkyries, and the more spiritual-quest kind of stories. This story is about temptation, and what we go through everyday and rarely stop to think about. Afterall, it's not about whether we are good or bad; it's about how hard can we fight temptation.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4555924003313085161" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


