<div id="review_1919266004" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1919266004" />
    <a title="Emmy Hermina Nathasia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/52663173-emmy-hermina-nathasia"><img alt="Emmy Hermina Nathasia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1546240178p2/52663173.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1919266004?book_show_action=true">Jun 12, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Emmy Hermina Nathasia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Emmy Hermina Nathasia" href="/user/show/52663173-emmy-hermina-nathasia">Emmy Hermina Nathasia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780060528003" href="/book/show/53812.The_Devil_and_Miss_Prym">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52663173-emmy-hermina-nathasia?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52663173-emmy-hermina-nathasia?shelf=1994-2015">1994-2015</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1919266004" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7670557973744802204">I just love, love, loveee this book. My 4th re-read and each time I never failed to be amazed the message delivered in the book. There is no straightforward answer as to whether human beings are good or bad, but instead it is a matter of individual choice. In terms of conclusions about Good and Evil, its up to the reader to decide. It would seem the way a reader see the subject of God and religion will determine the conclusion.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


